<SLUG> BC-BBN-DODGERNOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
INJURY PLAGUE WILL NOT ABATE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RICH HAMMOND  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM, Calif. _ The gray cloud that seems to be hovering over
the Los Angeles Dodgers' clubhouse got a little darker Saturday
afternoon when another important contributor limped off the field.
</P>
<P>
   Center fielder Todd Hollandsworth strained his right hamstring
while making a tough catch on a fly ball by Tim Salmon with two
outs in the ninth inning. He will be re-evaluated today.
</P>
<P>
   ``It looks like a pretty good pull,'' manager Davey Johnson
said. ``We're already short-handed up here.''
</P>
<P>
   Hollandsworth had been playing center field and batting leadoff
in place of Devon White, out since May 3 with a partial
rotator-cuff tear. Third baseman Adrian Beltre (strained right
hamstring) and catcher Todd Hundley (strained right oblique muscle)
are also on the 15-day disabled list.
</P>
<P>
   Hollandsworth suffered the same injury last year in an April
exhibition game against the Angels. On Saturday, he chased Salmon's
fly ball into left-center at full speed and felt the pull on his
final stride.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was just full extension and everybody could see when it
happened,'' Hollandsworth said. ``All I can say is that it wasn't
as bad as last year, but it's still pretty sore.''
</P>
<P>
   More moves: The Dodgers made roster moves for the third time in
four days. The team placed reserve outfielder Geronimo Berroa (bone
bruise on left foot) on the 15-day disabled list and designated
reliever Trever Miller for assignment.
</P>
<P>
   Reliever Onan Masaoka and utility player Shawn Gilbert joined
the Dodgers from Triple-A Albuquerque less than an hour before
Saturday's game, and both played.
</P>
<P>
   Masaoka, who pitched one inning for Albuquerque on Friday night,
got the first two outs of the ninth inning but then gave up two
singles and was pulled in favor of Antonio Osuna.
</P>
<P>
   The Dodgers recalled Masaoka for the third time this season.
They sent him to Albuquerque on May 22, when Miller joined the team
after being claimed off waivers from the Philadelphia Phillies.
Miller made just two appearances with the Dodgers and allowed six
runs in 2 innings. Miller will be sent to Albuqerque if he clears
waivers.
</P>
<P>
   Gilbert entered as a defensive replacement in left field after
Hollandsworth's injury. Gilbert, a 35-year-old right-handed hitter
who can play several infield and outfield positions, was hitting
.319 for Albuquerque this year with one home run, 14 RBI and five
stolen bases. He also made one appearance on the mound and earned a
save for the Dukes.
</P>
<P>
   Coach returns: Pitching coach Claude Osteen arrived at Edison
Field in the sixth inning after being hospitalized overnight in
Irvine for treatment of a kidney stone. Osteen was taken to UCI
Medical Center before Friday's game after complaining of abdominal
pain.
</P>
<P>
   Infield shuffle: Kevin Elster played third base for the second
consecutive game but only the third time in his 13-year career.
</P>
<P>
   With Beltre on the disabled list, the Dodgers will try Elster, a
natural shortstop, at third base, and Cora, recalled Wednesday from
Albuquerque, at shortstop.
</P>
<P>
   In the first inning, Elster caught a line drive off the bat of
Darin Erstad on his only defensive opportunity of the game. Cora
had five assists and started a double play in the fourth inning,
when the Angels had runners on first and second with one out.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
