<P>
   ETHERNET (San Francisco) _ Ethernet, invented in 1973, is one of
the oldest formats for office computer networks. Its ability to
evolve to ever faster data speeds has kept it relevant for decades.
And now it may be poised to become a major force on the Internet _
potentially challenging the entrenched position of big
telecommunications carriers and leading equipment makers, like
Cisco. By John Markoff.
</P>
