getting bigger through acquisitions. But not every pick is a
winner. By Seth Schiesel.
</P>
<P>
   ECOMMERCE-COLUMN (Undated) _ The E-Commerce column: An analysis
of whether brick-and-mortar retailers are better off integrating
their online operations or keeping them at arm's length, for
sales-tax purposes. Many experts contend that consumers don't care
that much about sales taxes, and so retailers are better off
integrating _ as Victoria's Secret does _ rather than segregating,
as Barnes and Noble does. By Bob Tedeschi.
</P>
<P>
   CELEBRITY-AD-COLUMN (New York) _ In deciding whether to sign
celebrity athletes, marketers are increasingly looking for proven,
long-term performance rather than one-time feats like, say, winning
a Super Bowl or a World Series. By Stuart Elliott.
