<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TELEWEST-CHELLO-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BRITISH CABLE COMPANY SAID TO BE NEAR DEAL 
</HEADLINE>
   By ANDREW ROSS SORKIN   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONDON _ Telewest Communications PLC, Britain's second-largest
cable television company, is expected to announce as early as this
week that it will acquire a stake of about 10 percent in Chello
Broadband NV, executives close to the talks said Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
   Chello, which provides high-speed access to the Internet across
Europe, is a unit of United Pan-Europe Communications NV, the
European cable television company.
</P>
<P>
   It remains unclear how much Telewest would pay for the Chello
stake. Executives close to the talks also said United Pan-Europe
could take a big stake in Telewest as part of the deal.
</P>
<P>
   If the acquisition of the Chello stake proceeds, Telewest, whose
biggest shareholders include Microsoft and Liberty Media Group, a
unit of AT&AMP;T, would be taking a stake in the European equivalent of
At Home Corp., the high-speed Internet service provider in which
AT&AMP;T holds a controlling stake.
</P>
<P>
   It would also give Chello access to Telewest's cable customers
in Britain. Chello's high-speed Internet service is available in
nine countries served by the United Pan-Europe Communications cable
network.
</P>
<P>
   Chello, which had been planning to offer shares to the public on
May 31 on the Nasdaq and Amsterdam stock exchanges, postponed its
offering. Executives close to the companies said they were working
to reach a deal by the end of this week so they could proceed with
the initial offering. They cautioned, however, that as with any
deal, they could both still decide to abandon the effort.
</P>
<P>
   Executives close to the talks said it had been difficult to put
a value on Chello, because of the recent gyrations among technology
stocks. Before Chello's initial offering was first pulled, it had
planned to sell 27 million shares _ 10 percent of the company _ for
13 to 17 euros, or $12.30 to $16.08, each.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
