<HEADLINE>
THIS WEEK'S TV HIGHLIGHTS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
TODAY: Summer's version of ``Monday Night Football,'' without all
the talk of Rush Limbaugh joining the gang in the booth. And one of
the storylines should be Devils goalie Martin Brodeur, who made
Brett Hull and Mike Modano look like Ice Capades rejects on their
home damp floor in Game 3. Brodeur even got so bored with things he
flipped the puck over the glass with four minutes left and drew a
penalty -- just so he could kill it himself. NHL finals Game 4: New
Jersey at Dallas, Channel 7, 5 p.m. (ABC has the rest of the
series: Thursday's Game 5 at New Jersey and Saturday's Game 6 at
Dallas, if necessary, both at 5 p.m.) 
TUESDAY: Gotta admit, our interest in this interleague concept
starts to wane after the Dodgers-Angels weekend series. MLB:
Dodgers at Texas, Fox Sports West 2, 5:35 p.m.; San Francisco at
Angels, Fox Sports West, 7:05 p.m. (Channel 5 has Dodgers' Monday
game at 5:35 p.m., while FSN2 has Wednesday's series finale at
12:05 p.m.; FSW has Angels' Monday and Wednesday games at 7:05
p.m.) 
WEDNESDAY: This just in: NBC has broken format and agreed to
televise an important sporting event live, not just tonight, but
for the rest of the series. May sweeps must be over. NBA Finals
Game 1: Indiana at Lakers/Portland, Channel 4, 6 p.m. 
THURSDAY: Tonight's MTV Movie Awards show won't have Dennis Rodman
or Shaquille O'Neal to kick around. We'll have to be content with
another odd event - this rain make-up game at Dodger Stadium. MLB:
Houston at Dodgers, Fox Sports Net, 6 p.m. 
FRIDAY: Wanna know how funny Michael Richards' new show will be
this fall? Don't have to ask. By the time the NBA Finals coverage
is over, you'll have seen each episode during the commercial
breaks. NBA Finals Game 2: Indiana at Lakers/Portland, Channel 4, 6
p.m. 
SATURDAY: No Andre. No Pete. No Lindsay. By the end of this week,
maybe Monica. No worry, say the French. They'll have just as much
fun playing on the clay without those ugly Americans. Now, if
there's a way to guarantee Venus Williams will get to the finals
... !ital!ooooh, la la.!off! Tennis: French Open, women's final,
Channel 4, noon (NBC also has the men's final Sunday at 6 a.m.) 
SUNDAY: The Travel Channel's episode of ``Trailblazers'' is about
the Bushmen who who collect drops of water in the Kalahari Desert.
Interesting. But frankly, we're all Trailblazered out by this
point. NBA Finals Game 3: Lakers/Portland at Indiana, Channel 4,
4:30 p.m.
